.TH rom-weaver-bundle-parse 1  "rom-weaver-bundle-parse "
.SH NAME
rom\-weaver\-bundle\-parse \- Parse and validate a rom\-weaver\-bundle.json bundle (plain, stream\-codec compressed, or inside an archive) and resolve its ROM/patch entries
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBrom\-weaver bundle parse\fR [\fB\-\-extract\-dir\fR] [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-threads\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-trace\fR] [\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fISOURCE\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Parse and validate a rom\-weaver\-bundle.json bundle and resolve its ROM/patch entries.
.PP
Accepted sources: a plain rom\-weaver\-bundle.json, a stream\-codec\-compressed rom\-weaver\-bundle.json.gz/.bz2/.xz/.zst, or an archive carrying rom\-weaver\-bundle.json at its root (an "everything archive" that also bundles the ROM and patches).
.PP
Bundle `path` entries refer to archive members (or files next to the bundle). With \-\-extract\-dir, members referenced by the bundle are extracted there and returned as resolved paths, and extracted patch entries include a full patch descriptor. URL entries are returned verbatim; relative URLs resolve against the bundle\*(Aqs own location on the caller\*(Aqs side.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-extract\-dir\fR \fI<EXTRACT_DIR>\fR
Extract bundle\-referenced archive members into this directory (path entries stay unresolved without it when the source is an archive)
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit progress and terminal status as JSON lines
.TP
\fB\-\-progress\fR
Force running progress events on
.TP
\fB\-\-threads\fR \fI<auto|N>\fR [default: auto]
Thread budget: auto or a positive integer
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR
Disable running progress events
.TP
\fB\-\-trace\fR
Enable trace logs (also enabled by ROM_WEAVER_LOG or RUST_LOG)
.TP
\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR
Enable trace logs from dependencies (for example nod)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
<\fISOURCE\fR>
Bundle file or archive containing a root bundle
